g.ns107:text: $\\bullet$ NV center ensemble are promising room-temperature magnetometer \n\nbut are partly limited by the interactions between the spins.
$\\bullet$ Dipole-dipole interaction in dense ensemble of NV centers causes \n\nspin relaxation. The effect is stronger at low magnetic field.
$\\bullet$ Further studies on low field depolarization: temperature dependance, \n\nmaterial aspects...
$\\bullet$ LFDM applications: real-time magnetometry in liquids, \n\nbackground-free fluorescence microscopy, large NV magnetometers...
$\\bullet$ The low field depolarization effect can be used to create \n\nmicrowave-free and orientation-free magnetometers.
